programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Competitive Edge
programme.desc: As a teen, Luray used to go from the beach to a tanning booth. Now she's after a corporate career, and doesn't want to look like an old lady compared to the other job candidates.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Old Look Is In Remission
programme.desc: Bobbi's appearance has suffered greatly due to her constant medical treatments and recent mastectomy. After losing her hair and her left breast, she is ready for a change, and has called upon our team of experts to help her through the process.
programme.sub-title: The Old Look Is In Remission

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Overhauling Momma
programme.desc: Wendy's fought the battle of the bulge her entire life, but now she's gone from a size 30 to a size 6 and is enjoying a more active lifestyle. Dermatology and cosmetic dentistry bring her face in line with her new body. Will she go from tired to admired?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: She’s Cookin’ Now!
programme.desc: Wendy is a house cleaner with bigger aspirations. A single mother for 15 years, Wendy recently remarried, and with a duel income, it's time for her to follow her dreams of becoming a professional chef. The only problem – her looks aren't exactly 5 Star.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp
programme.desc: Presenter and stylist Nicky Hambleton-Jones uses every trick in the book to make someone look dramatically younger. What will it take to transform the bedraggled and drawn features of prison officer Bernie Sharp?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sharon Evans
programme.desc: 45 year old Welsh farmer Sharon Evans has so many animals to tend to that she's stopped looking after herself. Nicky Hambleton-Jones calls in the full cavalry on this one. Standby for one of the most breathtaking transformations of the series.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Oh, To Be a Kid Again!
programme.desc: Katrina dropped out of school and became a needed parent to her younger siblings. Her looks went south and her social life became non-existent, so Katrina turned to food for comfort. Time to make Katrina look 10 Years Younger!
programme.sub-title: Oh, To Be a Kid Again!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Turning That Frown Upside Down
programme.desc: Angela's made such a habit of hiding her discolored teeth that she's developed a permanent frown. She's pursuing a career as a comedienne, but it's hard for her to laugh about the state of her looks. She feels like the clock is ticking.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From ‘Stache to Flash
programme.desc: Jerry, a caring husband, father of three, and new grandfather, has been hiding his teeth behind a moustache for years! With his style stuck in the 70's, it's our goal to help Jerry flash forward as we try to make Jerry look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Carole Ward
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 47-year-old Carole Ward who feels very unglamorous.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's the grand reopening of Mara and a British wildlife charity is using the event to release a vulture back into the wild. Fatani, the new, young and ambitious manager of Mara has hired Danny as the vet to oversee the release.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: The Embassy
programme.desc: Queenslander Sam and his German girlfriend Sandra met and fell in love in Thailand. After a long distance relationship, they've finally decided to leave their respective countries and begin a life together in Chiang Mail.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Former school teacher Jacob has been locked up in a Thai prison for the past 9 months, awaiting trial for a high grade drug trafficking offence. Young Maroubra-boy James arrives at the Embassy for a new passport claiming it was lost.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Big Families: Can't Stop, Won't Stop
programme.desc: We meet three families who are either expecting or planning a baby at the same time as seeing their older children, grow up, move out and start their own families.

programme.title: Big Families: Sibling Rivalry
programme.desc: Our first family have 10 children between the ages of a few months and their early teens. With all of the children so close in age, all of the kids are still at a stage where they desperately need their parents love and attention.

programme.title: Big Families: Price and Prejudice
programme.desc: Our first family are determined not to take government handouts. Dad works, mum stays at home and does the odd job and they budget to stay afloat. In their opinion, it was their choice to have 12 children so it's their responsibility to look after them.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 14
programme.desc: Today, we are going to look back at the highlight of last week. The 24 hour race - as always it was exciting. In addition 'Strong Man Run' and a look at the tourist drivers.

programme.title: Track Masters
programme.desc: Some heavy guns are going to be driven around the ring on today's show. We are at the Truck Grand Prix and shall be following the progress of driver Uwe Nittle as he gets ready for qualifying.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 16
programme.desc: On today's show, we will be taking a look at the RCN Challenge - the BMW Driving Experience. Also on the show, we will be paying a visit to the Devils Diner - the indoor meeting place for drivers on the ring!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 17
programme.desc: Now that the 24-hour race is over we have left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where Räder Sport is based. Famous for really fast front-wheel drives, it provides a lot of horsepower down on the track.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 18
programme.desc: The roaring sounds of engines and exhausts usually dominate the Nürburgring but on today's episode, we're focusing on something a little quieter. Ever fancied a 15-mile bike ride around the ring, or perhaps a 16-mile run?

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 19
programme.desc: On today's episode, we are going old-timer crazy, like the Mercedes S for example with 160 horsepower that lead Rudolf Caracciola to victory in the 1927 opening race. Do not to miss this old-timer grand prix event!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 20
programme.desc: Phoenix Racing, the successful team from the Eifel Region rocks the DTM. We will be showing you some pit stop training with the Swiss rookie Rahel Frey, a Ford GT kit car and a tuned Honda with a Spaniard at the wheel!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 21
programme.desc: Today on the Nürburgring: Patrick is tearing up the track in an Aston Martin Zagato with 12 cylinders of pure sound! Also on the show: a hummer, a Bremer Clio and a Frenchman in a Ferrari!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 22
programme.desc: Patrick makes André sweat! Also on the show: tourists from all over the world have made their way down to the Green Hell including many Germans, Austrians and five crazy Englishmen in a taxi!

programme.title: Tuning: Alpina / Mercedes
programme.desc: Tuning has to be conspicuous - not for Alpina.The B6 is the best example that Alpina has a penchant for understatement. We tested whether there is more to the Alpina B6 than meets the eye.

programme.title: Tuning: BMW / Chevrolet / Audi
programme.desc: The Kelleners Sport 640i is based on one of the most beautifully designed current 4-door coupés. The tuning forge of racing driver Ralf Kelleners specialises in the conversion of BMWs.

programme.title: Tuning: Dodge / Mini Cooper / Porsche
programme.desc: The Dodge RAM is anything but cute. It is a true beast. The ram is the symbol of the Dodge brand and the eponym for a very special vehicle. The RAM pickup combines robustness and impulsiveness.

programme.title: Tuning: Lamborghini / Porsche / Jaguar
programme.desc: A supercharger from O.CT gives the Lamborghini Huracan, which is by no means underpowered, an additional 200 hp. This makes the super sports car the ultimate street-legal projectile.

programme.title: 4x4: Wildly through the desert
programme.desc: In 2010, BMW and the German racing team X-Raid decided to transform a Mini Countryman into an offroad-vehicle and participate in the world-famous Dakar Rally. Also: the Mercedes G63 AMG 6x6, a most exclusive, over-the-top 6-wheel off-road monster...

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Joining
programme.desc: An excavation team unleashes a very dangerous Taelon on Earth. Siobhan Beckett comes over to America. She suspects Lili of being a spy and investigates.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First of its Kind
programme.desc: Following Boone's confrontation with Hegel that left him severely injured, he was eliminated by Zo'or. Beckett who was impregnated by Hegel gives birth to a boy who immediately grows up to a man.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Avatus

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: A Stitch in Time

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Dimensions

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Moonscape
programme.desc: Augur is forced to take part in a Taelon experiment. Da'an and Liam try to convince Zo'or that altering minds and implanting humans to make them aggressive to fight the Jaridians is not the correct path. Maiya makes contact with Sandoval.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Sleepers
programme.desc: A Jaridian probe lands on Earth and begins sucking energy from the Comonality. The Taelons use humans in a near-death state to keep their connection while Lili and Sandoval try to find out what is draining the energy.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Fissures
programme.desc: When large scale blackouts begin to occur in cities with portals, Taelon technology is blamed. Augur and Liam investigate the death of a portal worker by a strange creature that feeds on energy and is particularly attracted to the Taelons.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Get Out of This House

programme.title: Paranormal State: Church of the Damned

programme.title: Paranormal State: Ghost On the Tracks

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Sex Dungeon
programme.desc: Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey and Chad Calek join PRS for this unusual case of a sprawling mansion on Greyhaven Island near Detroit. Ken, the owner, hears voices and banging and it has him feeling both watched and cursed; a prisoner in his own home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Death Room
programme.desc: PRS arrives in Ryan's hometown to help the new owner of an old southern plantation unearth its dark history.?A painful family secret reveals a tale of greed and neglect, and the team must help free its unwilling victim from her spiritual prison.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Family Ties
programme.desc: Jimmie is haunted by the apparition of a mysterious old woman who peers at him in the bathroom of his family's Petersburg, VA home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Supernatural Seduction
programme.desc: PRS investigates the Campbell House, where the Innkeeper and guests claim to have sexual encounters with a spirit who has deep ties to a family tragedy.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dead Legends
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey investigate the famed Hotel Conneaut in northern Pennsylvania. Heavy doors opening on their own, sightings of a boy, a bride and a menacing butcher have the hotel's staff on edge.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fury
programme.desc: Kathy, her two daughters and her new husband, "Farmer" thought they had the perfect, quiet life deep in the mountains of West Virginia.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hostage to Fear
programme.desc: P.R.S. is summoned to help a family who has been haunted for years by spirits lurking in the house. Upon arrival the team finds a family that has become prisoners in their own home.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Leith Hall
programme.desc: Murders, strange noises and an apparition of a wounded soldier take the team to Leith Hall. Grey mists, eerie music and the spectral image of a white lady all lie in wait for the "Most Haunted" team.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Aberglasney House
programme.desc: Multiple deaths, a curse and many hauntings draw the "Most Haunted" team to the bizarre Aberglasney House in Wales.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Schooner Hotel
programme.desc: The team investigates the Schooner Inn, a 17th-century hotel with a history of murders, suicides and massacres; babies have been reportedly thrown into fires, and sixty ghosts are said to reside there.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Fitz Manor
programme.desc: Ghostly apparitions, poltergeists and secret tunnels await the "Most Haunted" team as they visit Fitz Manor, located in the heart of rural Shropshire and overlooking the River Severn.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Muckleburgh

programme.title: Most Haunted: Galleries of Justice

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tamworth Castle
programme.desc: Tamworth Castle is allegedly haunted by, among others, an particularly malicious spirit. Derek picks up on many spirits, including a Spanish executioner whose sword hangs in the great hall.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Monster - Part 2

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Good Doctor
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark go to work at a football team. They learn that one of the players has been getting drugs from the team doctor.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Alone
programme.desc: A homeless boy wishes that someone would love him.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Close Encounters of the Heavenly Kind
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark help a bullied orphan whose eccentric grandfather is in danger of losing him to a heartless social worker.
programme.sub-title: Close Encounters of the Heavenly Kind

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Change of Life
programme.desc: Mark switches places with an attractive movie star who has a low opinion of men.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Keep Smiling
programme.desc: Jonathan must help his own widow regain her love for life.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Last Assignment
programme.desc: An errant angel has been on probation for two centuries because he's always breaking the rules.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Carole Ward
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 47-year-old Carole Ward who feels very unglamorous.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Scrubs to Stilettos
programme.desc: Lisa works double shifts as a nurse and is also a single mom to a teenage son. After burning the candle at both ends for so long, it is finally showing up in her appearance. Our team is going to give this busy career mom some serious pampering.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Breaking Ground On A New Look
programme.desc: Dane's been working in the sun without coverage since he was 14 years old, and hasn't been to the dentist in 13 years. He's a derm and dental bad boy who needs to be scared straight, not only for himself, but for his daughters and fiancé as well.
programme.sub-title: Breaking Ground On A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Starting Over
programme.desc: Elyse is a recently divorced mother of two, trying to start her new life. She has found it difficult to stay in shape, and feels stress, UV rays and time have caught up with her. Now ready to re-enter the dating game, our coaches help get her into shape.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Runaway Ready
programme.desc: Joslyn modeled in college, and was a woman who always took care of the way she looked. After becoming a mother, the years of neglect have caught up to her. Will our experts be able to make Joslyn runway ready?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Time For Dad
programme.desc: David is a fire captain at work and has a wife and seven kids at home. His responsibilities have taken their toll, and he feels like an old man of the firehouse. Can David's look go from lukewarm to smoldering?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Janice Holmes
programme.desc: Wife and mother, Janice Holmes,42, was used to living it large. Then she lost more than three stone in weight, and stubbed out her forty-a-day fag habit, to become a picture of health.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Kim Edgecombe
programme.desc: Fiona McDonald and the "10 Years" team of experts gear up for their toughest challenge yet! Kim Edgecombe is living proof that smoking really does cause premature aging. Kim needs help, but are the team too late?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Heather Williams Re-Visit
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones revisits 42-year-old Heather Williams from Essex.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Pageantry Days Once Again
programme.desc: Marci is a former pageant girl, but kids, stress and lack of attention to her looks have sent her appearance south. With the help of a rare triple dose of doctor treatments and a Glam Squad overhaul, Marci hopes to remove the years of neglect.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power
programme.desc: Serial socialiser and budding nightclub entrepreneur Richard Power knows he looks old for his age. But even when a poll of 100 people confirm his thoughts he has difficulty accepting it's because he's drinking 35 pints a week and 40 cigarettes a day.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Shirley Maddison
programme.desc: Shirley's lack of self confidence stems from her poor self image. She thinks she looks old. She's not the only one. A public poll guessed her age at 52. The time for serious intervention has arrived from Nicky Hambleton-Jones.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: All is quiet at Leopard's Den as Sarah, Evan and Olivia gather at the hospital. Danny has been given the all clear to go home. But Du Plessis is still unconscious and seriously ill. Caroline keeps a tender vigil at his bedside.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New lodges nearly break the family, but they learn that it's the animals which make Leopard's Den a success.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny needs an assistant but fails to see that she's right under his nose; Sarah finds out that she needs her mum.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den expands and DuPlessis becomes a grandfather after a close-call with an angry elephant.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Sarah let their past catch up with them, and Caroline and DuPlessis go shopping for lion-prey.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: A white lion brings mixed fortunes to the family and Rosie is asked the big question. Amy Kriel is the last person you expect in Africa.

programme.title: Big Families: Price and Prejudice
programme.desc: Our first family are determined not to take government handouts. Dad works, mum stays at home and does the odd job and they budget to stay afloat. In their opinion, it was their choice to have 12 children so it's their responsibility to look after them.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Thomas and Jensen
programme.desc: The doctors meet nine-year-old Thomas who is very rigid in his thought patterns and finds change difficult. Thomas's parents, Nicola and Joe, want to find out what is causing his behaviour and what can be done to help him.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Bobby and Jessi-Jai
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Bobby, who won't eat anything except chocolate, sweets, cakes, chips, cheese, yoghurt and baked beans. Has Bobby got a food phobia and what can his parents do to help him try new healthy foods?

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Charlie and Billy
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Charlie who can become so destructive and violent that his mum has had to call the police. After meeting him, Dr Ravi and the experts think that a controversial new diagnosis may be the reason for Charlie's behaviour.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save two teenage girls fighting for their lives after their car crashed and rolled the Waiwera Hill.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: On Great Mercury Island near Coromandel, a scuba diver has surfaced unconscious without a pulse. Without Rescue 1 he may soon be dead.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team respond to a call out where an elderly couple in their 60s are in a critical condition after a head on collision.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: A truck driver who had one leg amputated 40 years ago, has crashed his truck and crushed his remaining leg. If Rescue 1 can't get him to hospital in time, he will bleed to death.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: Westpac chopper paramedic Bruce Kerr has a frantic battle to save a car crash victim with a life-threatening head injury.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save a 39 year old forestry worker who has been struck on the head leaving him paralyzed from the waist down.

programme.title: 4x4: Wildly through the desert
programme.desc: In 2010, BMW and the German racing team X-Raid decided to transform a Mini Countryman into an offroad-vehicle and participate in the world-famous Dakar Rally. Also: the Mercedes G63 AMG 6x6, a most exclusive, over-the-top 6-wheel off-road monster...

programme.title: 4x4: Trendy City - SUVs
programme.desc: City-SUVs are the latest trend in the automotive world. They aren't necessarily made for offroad terrain but attract customers through their modern and urban design. In this episode, the Subaru XV shows its offroad skills, and the Nissan Juke is take…

programme.title: 4x4: Land Rover Special
programme.desc: The Land Rover Defender is one of the oldest offroad car models. It may be loud and uncomfortable, but it's absolutely authentic in its simplicity. We took a look at this iconic vehicle and 70 years of Land Rover history.

programme.title: 4x4: Extraordinary SUVs
programme.desc: This Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid is the world's first hybrid SUV with two electric motors and a 2-liter combustion engine. We tested if such a combination makes sense for offroad vehicles. Also: the Chevrolet Silverado...

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Girlpower
programme.desc: Nancy and Nadia, two daring Jordanian women faced the challenge to cross the Moroccan desert in a Hummer H3. The two professional racers took part in the Conti 4x4 Trophy - a demanding rally through the Atlas Mountains and the Western Sahara.

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Concepts
programme.desc: Before Bentley and Jaguar started producing their own luxury SUV models, the two British brands presented their take on this special range of cars. We took a look at their concept cars, the Bentley EXP 9F and Jaguar's C-X17.

programme.title: 4x4: Normal vs. Lifestyle SUVs
programme.desc: The SUVs Nissan X-Trail and BMW X4 certainly aren't typical offroaders. We witnessed Nissan's presentation of their new X-Trail model and the BMW X4 world premiere in Bilbao. Also: the Steinbeißer Trophy...

programme.title: 4x4: American SUVs
programme.desc: In the United States, SUVs aren't usually considered simple workhorses but rather treated as regular everyday vehicles. US-Americans don't want to miss out on space, comfort and loading capacity. Their motto is: the bigger, the better.

programme.title: 4x4: Tuned SUVs
programme.desc: SUVs usually are rather impressive right out of the factory, but there are many tuning and customizing options: huge wheels, crazy colors and perfomance similar to super sports cars. One might ask if such alterations are really necessary, but enthusi…

programme.title: 4x4: Small, strong, stylish
programme.desc: At first glance, compact cars like the Audi A1, the Volkswagen Golf and the Mini don't seem to belong in this series, but when the "A1" becomes the "S1" and the Golf gets a "R" in its name, these small cars turn into all-wheel beasts.

programme.title: 4x4: Fascination offroad
programme.desc: At the All-Wheel Adventure in Bad Kissingen, Germany, the biggest exhibition for offroaders in Europe, we test drove the Rallye Defender and examined how a regular Jeep Wrangler with only a few modifications could double in price.

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on snow
programme.desc: In winter, when the streets get slippery, an all-wheel drive vehicle brings many advantages as you gain more traction. Under icy conditions we experienced one day in snowy Austria with rally professional Niki Schelle in a Suzuki SX4 S-Cross.

programme.title: 4x4: Rallye Fun
programme.desc: Countryside tours aren't the only option with an all-wheel drive car. You can also have a lot of fun on gravel roads. We show how that goes in a Subaru WRX STI. Also: in the 1990s, Ford had a successful go at international rally competitions...
